Stereotypes annotations help us to create spring beans automatically in applicationContext.

@Component
    \
     @Service
    \ 
     @Repository
    \
     @Controller


@Component is used as general on top of any JAVA Class. It is the base for other annotations.
It is used for any utility class or any generic class for which any general object is required in applicationContext


@Service - JAVA Class Having a Business Logic or logic for making external API calls. Present in Service Layer

@Repository - Codes Related to Database Operations. Like Retive, Update, Insert. Any DAO Classes in the Proeject. You can keep @Repository on top of that.

@Controller -  Present in Controller Layer.


